ZH: 我喜欢睡觉。
EN: I like to sleep.
ZH: 他每天晚上十点就会睡觉。
EN: He goes to bed at 10 o'clock every night.
ZH: 我昨晚很晚才睡觉。
EN: I slept very late last night.
ZH: 妈妈说小孩子要早睡早起。
EN: Mom says kids should go to bed early and wake up early.
ZH: 考试前不要熬夜，要保证充足的睡眠。
EN: Don't stay up late before the exam, make sure you get enough sleep.
ZH: 睡觉前最好不要喝咖啡。
EN: It's best not to drink coffee before going to bed.
ZH: 我们可以睡在这个舒适的床上。
EN: We can sleep on this comfortable bed.
ZH: 好好休息一下，今晚早点睡觉。
EN: Take a good rest and go to bed early tonight.
ZH: 我们下午可以小睡一会儿。
EN: We can take a nap in the afternoon.
ZH: 我经常做噩梦，所以不太喜欢睡觉。
EN: I often have nightmares, so I don't like to sleep much.
ZH: 他昨天下午睡了一整个小时。
EN: He slept for a whole hour yesterday afternoon.
ZH: 听音乐可以帮助我入睡。
EN: Listening to music helps me fall asleep.
ZH: 整夜都无法入睡让我感到非常沮丧。
EN: Not being able to fall asleep all night makes me feel very frustrated.
ZH: 在火车上睡觉不太方便。
EN: It's not very convenient to sleep on the train.
ZH: 我今天早上睡眠不足，感觉很疲倦。
EN: I didn't get enough sleep this morning and feel very tired.
ZH: 在飞机上睡觉不太容易，因为太吵了。
EN: It's not easy to sleep on a plane because it's too noisy.
ZH: 我喜欢躺在床上听音乐入睡。
EN: I like to lie in bed and listen to music to fall asleep.
ZH: 睡眠质量对我们的健康非常重要。
EN: Sleep quality is very important for our health.
